item.title: Problem 3233 Find the Count of Numbers Which Are Not Special
item.description: Problem Statement Link - Problem 3233 Question You are given 2 positive integers l and r. For any number x, all positive divisors of x except x are called the proper divisors of x. A number is called special if it has exactly 2 proper divisors. For example: The number 4 is special because it has proper divisors 1 and 2. The number 6 is not special because it has proper divisors 1, 2, and 3.
